The paper presents a novel method that uses machine learning models for battery life prediction based on comprehensive and real-time usage traces collected from smartphones. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it heavily relies on machine learning models. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the user experience of smartphones, which could fall under the sub-category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also deals with system status, sensor indicators, system events, and app status, which could be related to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of a statistical metric called the concordance index, which could be related to the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with smartphone usage traces, which could be related to the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM).
